messages.message: Travis build is errorring on my PR (not failing), I kicked off another build and it errorred as well with `The job exceeded the maximum log length, and has been terminated.` at the end of the log: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/16763/checks?check_run_id=1489960856. Build log: https://travis-ci.com/github/instabase/instabase/builds/206111709. I’m not sure what’s happening here and can’t find much information on specific “build errored” issue. I’m running `make run-py-unit-tests` locally to make sure everything passes but I don’t think this has to do with that. Would anyone know what’s going on?
@Felicia can you kick off another travis job and see if it works? Or also rebase / force push your branch again? Sorry for the bug!
no worries! i now rebased/force pushed - let’s see if its all good now :slightly_smiling_face: thanks
FWIW this has been happening to a lot of builds throughout the day. Has seemed to correct itself

Travis builds times out after 50 mins and apparently execution of all unit tests are taking longer than 50 mins.
So even after all the tests passes, timing out of build shows this error.
